    "id": 12,
    "title": "Measuring instruments : Height Guage and Puppy Dial ",
    "description": "This course contains below 2 Modules which are measuring instruments:\nHeight Guage\nPuppy Dial\n ",
    "video_url": "http://localhost:8000/static/videos/122222dc-478e-4b9b-bf81-258715d147d3.mp4",
    "created_by_id": 1,
    "objectives": "## Objectives\n- Understand the proper use of vernier calipers and height gauges for measuring length and height of objects.\n- Learn the procedure for checking parallelism using a dial gauge and understand the concept of parallelism in measurement.\n- Familiarize with the concept of number of turns and how to measure it, including understanding the direction of measurement (clockwise or anti-clockwise).",
    "applications": "## Definitions\n- **Bernier Caliper**: \u090f\u0915 \u0909\u092a\u0915\u0930\u0923 \u091c\u093f\u0938\u0915\u093e \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u0932\u0902\u092c\u093e\u0908 \u0915\u094b \u092e\u093e\u092a\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0947 \u0932\u093f\u090f \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948\u0964\n- **Height Gauge**: \u090f\u0915 \u0909\u092a\u0915\u0930\u0923 \u091c\u093f\u0938\u0915\u093e \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u090a\u0902\u091a\u093e\u0908 \u0915\u094b \u092e\u093e\u092a\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0947 \u0932\u093f\u090f \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948, \u091c\u094b 300mm \u0924\u0915 \u0915\u0940 \u0932\u0902\u092c\u093e\u0908 \u0915\u094b \u092e\u093e\u092a \u0938\u0915\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948\u0964\n- **Dial Gauge**: \u090f\u0915 \u0909\u092a\u0915\u0930\u0923 \u091c\u093f\u0938\u0915\u093e \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u092a\u0930\u093f\u0932\u0902\u092c\u0924\u093e (parallelism) \u0915\u094b \u092e\u093e\u092a\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0947 \u0932\u093f\u090f \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948\u0964\n- **Parallelism**: \u0926\u094b \u092f\u093e \u0926\u094b \u0938\u0947 \u0905\u0927\u093f\u0915 \u0938\u0924\u0939\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u0947 \u092c\u0940\u091a \u0915\u093e \u0938\u092e\u093e\u0928\u093e\u0902\u0924\u0930 \u0938\u0902\u092c\u0902\u0927, \u091c\u094b \u090f\u0915 \u0928\u093f\u0936\u094d\u091a\u093f\u0924 \u092e\u093e\u0928\u0915 \u0938\u0947 \u0905\u0927\u093f\u0915 \u0928\u0939\u0940\u0902 \u0939\u094b\u0928\u093e \u091a\u093e\u0939\u093f\u090f\u0964\n- **Spring Rate**: \u090f\u0915 \u0935\u0938\u094d\u0924\u0941 \u0915\u0947 \u0932\u091a\u0940\u0932\u0947\u092a\u0928 \u0915\u093e \u092e\u093e\u092a, \u091c\u094b \u0932\u094b\u0921 \u0914\u0930 \u0935\u093f\u0938\u094d\u0925\u093e\u092a\u0928 \u0915\u0947 \u092c\u0940\u091a \u0938\u0902\u092c\u0902\u0927 \u0915\u094b \u0926\u0930\u094d\u0936\u093e\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948\u0964\n- **Perpendicularity**: \u0926\u094b \u092f\u093e \u0926\u094b \u0938\u0947 \u0905\u0927\u093f\u0915 \u0938\u0924\u0939\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u0947 \u092c\u0940\u091a \u0915\u093e \u0932\u0902\u092c\u0935\u0924 \u0938\u0902\u092c\u0902\u0927\u0964\n\n## Practical Application\n- **\u0932\u0902\u092c\u093e\u0908 \u0915\u0940 \u091c\u093e\u0902\u091a**: \u092c\u0930\u0928\u093f\u092f\u0930 \u0915\u0948\u0932\u093f\u092a\u0930 \u092f\u093e \u0939\u093e\u0907\u091f \u0917\u0947\u091c \u0915\u093e \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u0915\u0930\u0915\u0947 \u0932\u0902\u092c\u093e\u0908 \u0915\u0940 \u091c\u093e\u0902\u091a \u0915\u0940 \u091c\u093e \u0938\u0915\u0924\u0940 \u0939\u0948\u0964\n- **\u092a\u0930\u093f\u0932\u0902\u092c\u0924\u093e \u0915\u0940 \u091c\u093e\u0902\u091a**: \u0921\u093e\u092f\u0932 \u0917\u0947\u091c \u0915\u093e \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u0915\u0930\u0915\u0947 \u092a\u0930\u093f\u0932\u0902\u092c\u0924\u093e \u0915\u0940 \u091c\u093e\u0902\u091a \u0915\u0940 \u091c\u093e \u0938\u0915\u0924\u0940 \u0939\u0948\u0964\n- **\u0932\u094b\u0921 \u092a\u0930\u0940\u0915\u094d\u0937\u0923**: \u0932\u094b\u0921 \u092a\u0930\u0940\u0915\u094d\u0937\u0923 \u092e\u0936\u0940\u0928 \u0915\u093e \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u0915\u0930\u0915\u0947 \u0935\u0938\u094d\u0924\u0941 \u0915\u0947 \u0932\u091a\u0940\u0932\u0947\u092a\u0928 \u0914\u0930 \u0905\u0928\u094d\u092f \u0917\u0941\u0923\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u093e \u092a\u0930\u0940\u0915\u094d\u0937\u0923 \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e \u0938\u0915\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948\u0964\n- **\u0928\u093f\u0930\u094d\u0926\u0947\u0936\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u093e \u092a\u093e\u0932\u0928**: \u0909\u092a\u0915\u0930\u0923\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u093e \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u0915\u0930\u0924\u0947 \u0938\u092e\u092f \u0928\u093f\u0930\u094d\u0926\u0947\u0936\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u093e \u092a\u093e\u0932\u0928 \u0915\u0930\u0928\u093e \u092e\u0939\u0924\u094d\u0935\u092a\u0942\u0930\u094d\u0923 \u0939\u0948, \u091c\u0948\u0938\u0947 \u0915\u093f \u091c\u0940\u0930\u094b \u092a\u0949\u0907\u0902\u091f \u0938\u0947\u091f \u0915\u0930\u0928\u093e \u0914\u0930 \u0938\u094d\u0915\u094d\u0930\u0940\u0928 \u0915\u094b \u091f\u091a \u0915\u0930\u0928\u093e\u0964\n- **\u092e\u093e\u092a \u0915\u0940 \u0938\u091f\u0940\u0915\u0924\u093e**: \u092e\u093e\u092a \u0915\u0940 \u0938\u091f\u0940\u0915\u0924\u093e \u0938\u0941\u0928\u093f\u0936\u094d\u091a\u093f\u0924 \u0915\u0930\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0947 \u0932\u093f\u090f \u0909\u092a\u0915\u0930\u0923\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u093e \u0938\u0939\u0940 \u0924\u0930\u0940\u0915\u0947 \u0938\u0947 \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u0915\u0930\u0928\u093e \u0914\u0930 \u092e\u093e\u092a \u0915\u094b \u0926\u094b\u0939\u0930\u093e\u0928\u093e \u092e\u0939\u0924\u094d\u0935\u092a\u0942\u0930\u094d\u0923 \u0939\u0948\u0964",
    "quiz_data": "[{\"question\": \"What is the primary function of a Height Gauge?\", \"options\": [\"A) To measure the parallelism of a surface\", \"B) To measure the length of an object\", \"C) To measure the height of an object\", \"D) To measure the spring rate of an object\"], \"correct_answer\": \"C) To measure the height of an object\", \"explanation\": \"The Height Gauge is used to measure the height of an object, with a range of up to 300mm.\"}, {\"question\": \"How do you zero a Height Gauge?\", \"options\": [\"A) By touching the base of the object to be measured\", \"B) By touching the surface plate to the base of the Height Gauge\", \"C) By rotating the dial until it reaches zero\", \"D) By using an external calibration device\"], \"correct_answer\": \"B) By touching the surface plate to the base of the Height Gauge\", \"explanation\": \"To zero a Height Gauge, you need to touch the surface plate to the base of the Height Gauge and then adjust the dial to zero.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the purpose of a Puppy Dial?\", \"options\": [\"A) To measure the length of an object\", \"B) To measure the height of an object\", \"C) To measure the parallelism of a surface\", \"D) To measure the spring rate of an object\"], \"correct_answer\": \"C) To measure the parallelism of a surface\", \"explanation\": \"The Puppy Dial is used to measure the parallelism of a surface, with an accuracy of up to 0.1mm.\"}, {\"question\": \"How do you measure the parallelism of a surface using a Puppy Dial?\", \"options\": [\"A) By rotating the dial until it reaches zero\", \"B) By touching the surface to be measured to the dial\", \"C) By using an external calibration device\", \"D) By rotating the surface until the dial reads zero\"], \"correct_answer\": \"B) By touching the surface to be measured to the dial\", \"explanation\": \"To measure the parallelism of a surface using a Puppy Dial, you need to touch the surface to be measured to the dial and then read the measurement.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the range of measurement for a Height Gauge?\", \"options\": [\"A) Up to 100mm\", \"B) Up to 200mm\", \"C) Up to 300mm\", \"D) Up to 400mm\"], \"correct_answer\": \"C) Up to 300mm\", \"explanation\": \"The range of measurement for a Height Gauge is up to 300mm.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the purpose of a load testing machine?\", \"options\": [\"A) To measure the length of an object\", \"B) To measure the height of an object\", \"C) To measure the spring rate of an object\", \"D) To measure the parallelism of a surface\"], \"correct_answer\": \"C) To measure the spring rate of an object\", \"explanation\": \"The load testing machine is used to measure the spring rate of an object.\"}, {\"question\": \"How do you measure the number of turns of an object?\", \"options\": [\"A) By counting the number of rotations\", \"B) By measuring the distance traveled\", \"C) By using a Puppy Dial\", \"D) By using a Height Gauge\"], \"correct_answer\": \"A) By counting the number of rotations\", \"explanation\": \"To measure the number of turns of an object, you need to count the number of rotations, with one turn equal to 360 degrees.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the direction of measurement for a Puppy Dial?\", \"options\": [\"A) Clockwise\", \"B) Anti-clockwise\", \"C) Either clockwise or anti-clockwise\", \"D) Depends on the object being measured\"], \"correct_answer\": \"A) Clockwise\", \"explanation\": \"The direction of measurement for a Puppy Dial is clockwise.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the accuracy of a Puppy Dial?\", \"options\": [\"A) Up to 0.01mm\", \"B) Up to 0.1mm\", \"C) Up to 1mm\", \"D) Up to 10mm\"], \"correct_answer\": \"B) Up to 0.1mm\", \"explanation\": \"The accuracy of a Puppy Dial is up to 0.1mm.\"}, {\"question\": \"How do you calibrate a Puppy Dial?\", \"options\": [\"A) By rotating the dial until it reaches zero\", \"B) By touching the surface to be measured to the dial\", \"C) By using an external calibration device\", \"D) By adjusting the dial to match a known measurement\"], \"correct_answer\": \"D) By adjusting the dial to match a known measurement\", \"explanation\": \"To calibrate a Puppy Dial, you need to adjust the dial to match a known measurement.\"}]",
    "is_processing": false
  },
  {
    "id": 14,
    "title": "First Part Approval",
    "description": "This is a module on First Part Approval: FPA",
    "video_url": "http://localhost:8000/static/videos/46d631b1-0ec2-4e18-8f8f-acead912f976.mp4",
    "created_by_id": 1,
    "objectives": "## Objectives\n- Understand the process of setting up and approving work orders, including the importance of sampling and meeting customer specifications.\n- Learn how to measure and analyze key dimensions, such as Y-Daya, ID, and length, to ensure they meet customer requirements.\n- Familiarize yourself with the various processes involved in manufacturing, including heat treatment, grinding, washing, and quality control checks.\n- Understand how to verify that final products meet customer specifications, including checking dimensions and performing quality control checks.\n- Learn how to use various measurement tools, such as vernier calipers and height gauges, to check dimensions and ensure accuracy.",
    "applications": "## Definitions\n- **In Process**: The stage of production where the product is being manufactured and its dimensions are being checked and fixed.\n- **Sampling Base**: A method of selecting a representative sample of products to check their dimensions and quality.\n- **FPA (First Part Approval)**: A process of approving the first part of a production run to ensure it meets the customer's specifications.\n- **Setting Approval Process**: A process of approving the settings and dimensions of a product before starting production.\n- **Y-Daya**: A measure of the variation in the diameter of a product, calculated as the average of the maximum and minimum diameters.\n- **ID (Inner Diameter)**: The inner diameter of a product, which is measured and checked against the customer's specifications.\n- **Heat Treatment**: A process of treating a product with heat to change its properties or structure.\n- **Grinding**: A process of smoothing or polishing a product's surface.\n- **Washing**: A process of cleaning a product's surface.\n\n## Practical Application\n- Checking the dimensions of a product during the in-process stage to ensure they meet the customer's specifications.\n- Using a sampling base to select a representative sample of products to check their dimensions and quality.\n- Implementing a First Part Approval (FPA) process to approve the first part of a production run.\n- Using a setting approval process to approve the settings and dimensions of a product before starting production.\n- Measuring the Y-Daya of a product to calculate the variation in its diameter.\n- Checking the inner diameter (ID) of a product against the customer's specifications.\n- Applying heat treatment, grinding, and washing processes to a product to change its properties or structure.\n- Using vernier calipers, height gauges, and other measuring instruments to check the dimensions of a product.\n- Comparing the final dimensions of a product against the customer's specifications to ensure they meet the requirements.",
    "quiz_data": "[{\"question\": \"What is the primary purpose of First Part Approval (FPA) in the manufacturing process?\", \"options\": [\"A) To inspect the final product\", \"B) To ensure that the in-process dimensions meet the customer's specifications\", \"C) To conduct a final quality check\", \"D) To analyze the sampling base\"], \"correct_answer\": \"B) To ensure that the in-process dimensions meet the customer's specifications\", \"explanation\": \"The primary purpose of FPA is to ensure that the in-process dimensions meet the customer's specifications, by analyzing the sampling base and checking if it meets the final specs.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the process used to analyze the sampling base in FPA?\", \"options\": [\"A) Setting approval process\", \"B) Heat treatment process\", \"C) Grinding process\", \"D) Washing process\"], \"correct_answer\": \"A) Setting approval process\", \"explanation\": \"The setting approval process is used to analyze the sampling base in FPA, to ensure that it meets the customer's specifications.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is Y-Daya, and how is it measured?\", \"options\": [\"A) Y-Daya is the diameter of the part, measured using a vernier caliper\", \"B) Y-Daya is the length of the part, measured using a height gauge\", \"C) Y-Daya is a dimension measured in the in-process stage, with a specific tolerance\", \"D) Y-Daya is the spring rate of the part, measured using a spring rate tester\"], \"correct_answer\": \"C) Y-Daya is a dimension measured in the in-process stage, with a specific tolerance\", \"explanation\": \"Y-Daya is a dimension measured in the in-process stage, with a specific tolerance, as mentioned in the transcript.\"}, {\"question\": \"What are the processes involved in the manufacturing of a part, after the sampling stage?\", \"options\": [\"A) Heat treatment, grinding, and washing\", \"B) Setting approval, heat treatment, and grinding\", \"C) Heat treatment, grinding, washing, and inspection\", \"D) Setting approval, heat treatment, grinding, washing, and inspection\"], \"correct_answer\": \"C) Heat treatment, grinding, washing, and inspection\", \"explanation\": \"The processes involved in the manufacturing of a part, after the sampling stage, are heat treatment, grinding, washing, and inspection, as mentioned in the transcript.\"}, {\"question\": \"How is the length of a part measured in the FPA process?\", \"options\": [\"A) Using a vernier caliper only\", \"B) Using a height gauge only\", \"C) Using both a vernier caliper and a height gauge\", \"D) Using a spring rate tester\"], \"correct_answer\": \"C) Using both a vernier caliper and a height gauge\", \"explanation\": \"The length of a part can be measured using both a vernier caliper and a height gauge, as mentioned in the transcript.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the purpose of checking the final dimensions of a part against the customer's specifications?\", \"options\": [\"A) To ensure that the part meets the in-process dimensions\", \"B) To ensure that the part meets the customer's specifications\", \"C) To conduct a final quality check\", \"D) To analyze the sampling base\"], \"correct_answer\": \"B) To ensure that the part meets the customer's specifications\", \"explanation\": \"The purpose of checking the final dimensions of a part against the customer's specifications is to ensure that the part meets the customer's specifications, as mentioned in the transcript.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the tolerance for the ID dimension, as per the customer's specification?\", \"options\": [\"A) 12 +/- 0.1\", \"B) 12 +/- 0.15\", \"C) 12 +/- 0.2\", \"D) 12 +/- 0.5\"], \"correct_answer\": \"B) 12 +/- 0.15\", \"explanation\": \"The tolerance for the ID dimension, as per the customer's specification, is 12 +/- 0.15, as mentioned in the transcript.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the purpose of the setting approval process in FPA?\", \"options\": [\"A) To inspect the final product\", \"B) To analyze the sampling base\", \"C) To ensure that the in-process dimensions meet the customer's specifications\", \"D) To conduct a final quality check\"], \"correct_answer\": \"C) To ensure that the in-process dimensions meet the customer's specifications\", \"explanation\": \"The purpose of the setting approval process in FPA is to ensure that the in-process dimensions meet the customer's specifications, by analyzing the sampling base.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the result of the FPA process, if the final dimensions of the part meet the customer's specifications?\", \"options\": [\"A) The part is rejected\", \"B) The part is accepted\", \"C) The part is reworked\", \"D) The part is inspected again\"], \"correct_answer\": \"B) The part is accepted\", \"explanation\": \"If the final dimensions of the part meet the customer's specifications, the result of the FPA process is that the part is accepted, as mentioned in the transcript.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the purpose of measuring the Y-Daya dimension in the in-process stage?\", \"options\": [\"A) To ensure that the part meets the customer's specifications\", \"B) To analyze the sampling base\", \"C) To conduct a final quality check\", \"D) To measure the spring rate of the part\"], \"correct_answer\": \"A) To ensure that the part meets the customer's specifications\", \"explanation\": \"The purpose of measuring the Y-Daya dimension in the in-process stage is to ensure that the part meets the customer's specifications, as mentioned in the transcript.\"}]",
    "is_processing": false
  },
  {
    "id": 15,
    "title": "Plug Guage",
    "description": "This is a Module on Plug Guage measuring instrument",
    "video_url": "http://localhost:8000/static/videos/3cda3b31-aaaa-4aad-8093-96c38001f9e7.mp4",
    "created_by_id": 1,
    "objectives": "## Objectives\n- Understand the role of a plug gauge in measuring and controlling ID (Inner Diameter) in a production process\n- Learn how to apply plug gauges in mass production to ensure quality control and adherence to customer specifications\n- Identify the importance of using plug gauges to determine whether a product meets the required specifications, using \"go\" and \"no-go\" gauges to make this determination",
    "applications": "## Definitions\n- **Plug**: \u090f\u0915 \u0909\u092a\u0915\u0930\u0923 \u091c\u094b \u0906\u0908\u0921\u0940 \u0915\u094b \u092e\u093e\u092a\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0947 \u0932\u093f\u090f \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948\u0964\n- **Plug Gauge**: \u090f\u0915 \u0909\u092a\u0915\u0930\u0923 \u091c\u094b \u0935\u093f\u0936\u093f\u0937\u094d\u091f \u092e\u093e\u092a\u0926\u0902\u0921\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u0947 \u0905\u0928\u0941\u0938\u093e\u0930 \u0935\u0938\u094d\u0924\u0941\u0913\u0902 \u0915\u094b \u092e\u093e\u092a\u0928\u0947 \u0914\u0930 \u0909\u0928\u0915\u0940 \u0917\u0941\u0923\u0935\u0924\u094d\u0924\u093e \u0915\u0940 \u091c\u093e\u0902\u091a \u0915\u0930\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0947 \u0932\u093f\u090f \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948\u0964\n- **Mass Production**: \u092c\u0921\u093c\u0947 \u092a\u0948\u092e\u093e\u0928\u0947 \u092a\u0930 \u0909\u0924\u094d\u092a\u093e\u0926\u0928, \u091c\u0939\u093e\u0902 \u0909\u0924\u094d\u092a\u093e\u0926\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u094b \u092c\u0921\u093c\u0940 \u092e\u093e\u0924\u094d\u0930\u093e \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092c\u0928\u093e\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948\u0964\n- **Quality Control**: \u0909\u0924\u094d\u092a\u093e\u0926\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u0940 \u0917\u0941\u0923\u0935\u0924\u094d\u0924\u093e \u0915\u0940 \u091c\u093e\u0902\u091a \u0914\u0930 \u0928\u093f\u092f\u0902\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0923 \u0915\u0930\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0940 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0915\u094d\u0930\u093f\u092f\u093e\u0964\n- **ID Control**: \u0906\u0902\u0924\u0930\u093f\u0915 \u0935\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938 \u0915\u094b \u0928\u093f\u092f\u0902\u0924\u094d\u0930\u093f\u0924 \u0915\u0930\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0940 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0915\u094d\u0930\u093f\u092f\u093e\u0964\n- **Go/No-Go**: \u090f\u0915 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0915\u093e\u0930 \u0915\u093e \u092e\u093e\u092a\u0926\u0902\u0921 \u091c\u094b \u092f\u0939 \u0928\u093f\u0930\u094d\u0927\u093e\u0930\u093f\u0924 \u0915\u0930\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948 \u0915\u093f \u0915\u094b\u0908 \u0935\u0938\u094d\u0924\u0941 \u0935\u093f\u0936\u093f\u0937\u094d\u091f \u092e\u093e\u092a\u0926\u0902\u0921\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u0947 \u0905\u0928\u0941\u0938\u093e\u0930 \u0939\u0948 \u092f\u093e \u0928\u0939\u0940\u0902\u0964\n\n## Practical Application\n- \u092a\u094d\u0932\u0917 \u0917\u0947\u091c \u0915\u093e \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u0909\u0924\u094d\u092a\u093e\u0926\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u0947 \u092e\u093e\u092a\u0926\u0902\u0921\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u0940 \u091c\u093e\u0902\u091a \u0915\u0930\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0947 \u0932\u093f\u090f \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e \u0938\u0915\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948, \u091c\u0948\u0938\u0947 \u0915\u093f \u0906\u0902\u0924\u0930\u093f\u0915 \u0935\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938 \u0915\u0940 \u091c\u093e\u0902\u091a \u0915\u0930\u0928\u093e\u0964\n- \u092e\u093e\u0938 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u094b\u0921\u0915\u094d\u0936\u0928 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092a\u094d\u0932\u0917 \u0917\u0947\u091c \u0915\u093e \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u0915\u0930\u0915\u0947 \u0909\u0924\u094d\u092a\u093e\u0926\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u0940 \u0917\u0941\u0923\u0935\u0924\u094d\u0924\u093e \u0915\u0940 \u091c\u093e\u0902\u091a \u0915\u0940 \u091c\u093e \u0938\u0915\u0924\u0940 \u0939\u0948 \u0914\u0930 \u092f\u0939 \u0938\u0941\u0928\u093f\u0936\u094d\u091a\u093f\u0924 \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e \u0938\u0915\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948 \u0915\u093f \u0935\u0947 \u0935\u093f\u0936\u093f\u0937\u094d\u091f \u092e\u093e\u092a\u0926\u0902\u0921\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u0947 \u0905\u0928\u0941\u0938\u093e\u0930 \u0939\u0948\u0902\u0964\n- \u0911\u092a\u0930\u0947\u091f\u0930 \u0914\u0930 \u0917\u0941\u0923\u0935\u0924\u094d\u0924\u093e \u0928\u093f\u0930\u0940\u0915\u094d\u0937\u0915\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u094b \u092a\u094d\u0932\u0917 \u0917\u0947\u091c \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0926\u093e\u0928 \u0915\u0930\u0915\u0947 \u0909\u0928\u094d\u0939\u0947\u0902 \u0909\u0924\u094d\u092a\u093e\u0926\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u0940 \u091c\u093e\u0902\u091a \u0915\u0930\u0928\u0947 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092e\u0926\u0926 \u092e\u093f\u0932 \u0938\u0915\u0924\u0940 \u0939\u0948\u0964\n- \u0917\u094b/\u0928\u094b-\u0917\u094b \u092e\u093e\u092a\u0926\u0902\u0921 \u0915\u093e \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u0915\u0930\u0915\u0947 \u092f\u0939 \u0928\u093f\u0930\u094d\u0927\u093e\u0930\u093f\u0924 \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e \u0938\u0915\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948 \u0915\u093f \u0915\u094b\u0908 \u0935\u0938\u094d\u0924\u0941 \u0935\u093f\u0936\u093f\u0937\u094d\u091f \u092e\u093e\u092a\u0926\u0902\u0921\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u0947 \u0905\u0928\u0941\u0938\u093e\u0930 \u0939\u0948 \u092f\u093e \u0928\u0939\u0940\u0902\u0964",
    "quiz_data": "[{\"question\": \"What is the primary function of the plug mentioned in the context?\", \"options\": [\"A) To measure the outer diameter\", \"B) To measure the inner diameter\", \"C) To measure the length\", \"D) To measure the width\"], \"correct_answer\": \"B) To measure the inner diameter\", \"explanation\": \"The plug is used to measure the inner diameter, as it is used for ID measurement.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the purpose of the plug gauge in mass production?\", \"options\": [\"A) To inspect the quality of the product\", \"B) To measure the dimensions of the product\", \"C) To assemble the product\", \"D) To package the product\"], \"correct_answer\": \"B) To measure the dimensions of the product\", \"explanation\": \"The plug gauge is used to measure the dimensions of the product in mass production.\"}, {\"question\": \"What type of production process is the plug gauge used in?\", \"options\": [\"A) Sampling\", \"B) Mass production\", \"C) Quality control\", \"D) Research and development\"], \"correct_answer\": \"B) Mass production\", \"explanation\": \"The plug gauge is used in mass production to measure the dimensions of the product.\"}, {\"question\": \"Who is provided with the plug gauge in the mass production process?\", \"options\": [\"A) Only the operator\", \"B) Only the quality inspector\", \"C) Both the operator and the quality inspector\", \"D) Neither the operator nor the quality inspector\"], \"correct_answer\": \"C) Both the operator and the quality inspector\", \"explanation\": \"Both the operator and the quality inspector are provided with the plug gauge in the mass production process.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the purpose of the plug gauge in terms of measurement?\", \"options\": [\"A) To provide an approximate measurement\", \"B) To provide a perfect measurement\", \"C) To provide a rough estimate\", \"D) To provide a range of measurements\"], \"correct_answer\": \"B) To provide a perfect measurement\", \"explanation\": \"The plug gauge is used to provide a perfect measurement, as it is applicable for perfect measuring.\"}]",
    "is_processing": false
  },
  {
    "id": 16,
    "title": "Load Testing Machine",
    "description": "This Module is about measuring instrument which is called Load Testing Machine. ",
    "video_url": "http://localhost:8000/static/videos/97ab567b-2d73-41f0-b3e3-eec34086988a.mp4",
    "created_by_id": 1,
    "objectives": "## Objectives\n- Understand the operating procedure of a load testing machine and its components, such as the load cell and base plate.\n- Learn how to set up and calibrate the machine for testing, including zeroing the length and weight measurements.\n- Understand how to conduct a load test on a specimen at a specified length and record the resulting load measurement.\n- Interpret the results of the load test and compare them to the required specifications.\n- Familiarize oneself with the machine's functionality and limitations in measuring load at specific compression lengths.",
    "applications": "## Definitions\n- **Load Testing Machine**: \u090f\u0915 \u092e\u0936\u0940\u0928 \u091c\u094b \u0935\u093f\u0936\u093f\u0937\u094d\u091f \u0926\u092c\u093e\u0935 \u0932\u0902\u092c\u093e\u0908 \u092a\u0930 \u0932\u094b\u0921 \u0915\u094b \u092e\u093e\u092a\u0924\u0940 \u0939\u0948\u0964\n- **Compression Length**: \u0935\u0939 \u0932\u0902\u092c\u093e\u0908 \u091c\u093f\u0938 \u092a\u0930 \u0932\u094b\u0921 \u0915\u094b \u092e\u093e\u092a\u093e \u091c\u093e\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948\u0964\n- **Load Cell**: \u090f\u0915 \u0909\u092a\u0915\u0930\u0923 \u091c\u094b \u0932\u094b\u0921 \u0915\u094b \u092e\u093e\u092a\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948\u0964\n- **Operating Procedure**: \u092e\u0936\u0940\u0928 \u0915\u093e \u0938\u0902\u091a\u093e\u0932\u0928 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0915\u094d\u0930\u093f\u092f\u093e, \u091c\u093f\u0938\u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092e\u0936\u0940\u0928 \u0915\u094b \u0936\u0942\u0928\u094d\u092f \u0915\u0930\u0928\u093e, \u0932\u094b\u0921 \u0938\u0947\u0932 \u0915\u094b \u0938\u094d\u0925\u093e\u092a\u093f\u0924 \u0915\u0930\u0928\u093e, \u0914\u0930 \u0935\u093f\u0936\u093f\u0937\u094d\u091f \u0932\u0902\u092c\u093e\u0908 \u092a\u0930 \u0932\u094b\u0921 \u0915\u094b \u092e\u093e\u092a\u0928\u093e \u0936\u093e\u092e\u093f\u0932 \u0939\u0948\u0964\n- **Specified Length**: \u0935\u0939 \u0932\u0902\u092c\u093e\u0908 \u091c\u093f\u0938 \u092a\u0930 \u0932\u094b\u0921 \u0915\u094b \u092e\u093e\u092a\u093e \u091c\u093e\u0928\u093e \u0939\u094b\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948\u0964\n- **Unit of Measurement**: \u0915\u093f\u0932\u094b\u0917\u094d\u0930\u093e\u092e (\u0915\u0947\u091c\u0940) \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0932\u094b\u0921 \u0915\u0940 \u0907\u0915\u093e\u0908\u0964\n\n## Practical Application\n- \u0932\u094b\u0921 \u091f\u0947\u0938\u094d\u091f\u093f\u0902\u0917 \u092e\u0936\u0940\u0928 \u0915\u093e \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u0935\u093f\u0936\u093f\u0937\u094d\u091f \u0932\u0902\u092c\u093e\u0908 \u092a\u0930 \u0932\u094b\u0921 \u0915\u094b \u092e\u093e\u092a\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0947 \u0932\u093f\u090f \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948, \u091c\u0948\u0938\u0947 \u0915\u093f 10mm \u092a\u0930 1 \u0915\u093f\u0932\u094b\u0917\u094d\u0930\u093e\u092e \u0932\u094b\u0921\u0964\n- \u092e\u0936\u0940\u0928 \u0915\u094b \u0936\u0942\u0928\u094d\u092f \u0915\u0930\u0928\u0947 \u0914\u0930 \u0932\u094b\u0921 \u0938\u0947\u0932 \u0915\u094b \u0938\u094d\u0925\u093e\u092a\u093f\u0924 \u0915\u0930\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0947 \u0932\u093f\u090f \u090f\u0915 \u0935\u093f\u0936\u093f\u0937\u094d\u091f \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0915\u094d\u0930\u093f\u092f\u093e \u0915\u093e \u092a\u093e\u0932\u0928 \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948\u0964\n- \u0932\u094b\u0921 \u0938\u0947\u0932 \u0915\u093e \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u0932\u094b\u0921 \u0915\u094b \u092e\u093e\u092a\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0947 \u0932\u093f\u090f \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948, \u0914\u0930 \u0907\u0938\u0915\u093e \u0935\u091c\u0928 \u092d\u0940 \u092e\u093e\u092a\u093e \u091c\u093e\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948\u0964\n- \u092e\u0936\u0940\u0928 \u0915\u093e \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u0935\u093f\u092d\u093f\u0928\u094d\u0928 \u0932\u0902\u092c\u093e\u0907\u092f\u094b\u0902 \u092a\u0930 \u0932\u094b\u0921 \u0915\u094b \u092e\u093e\u092a\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0947 \u0932\u093f\u090f \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e \u0938\u0915\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948, \u091c\u0948\u0938\u0947 \u0915\u093f 28.44mm \u092a\u0930 1.017 \u0915\u093f\u0932\u094b\u0917\u094d\u0930\u093e\u092e \u0932\u094b\u0921\u0964\n- \u092a\u0930\u093f\u0923\u093e\u092e\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u094b \u0930\u093f\u0915\u0949\u0930\u094d\u0921 \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e \u0938\u0915\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948 \u0914\u0930 \u0935\u093f\u0936\u093f\u0937\u094d\u091f \u0906\u0935\u0936\u094d\u092f\u0915\u0924\u093e\u0913\u0902 \u0915\u0947 \u0938\u093e\u0925 \u0924\u0941\u0932\u0928\u093e \u0915\u0940 \u091c\u093e \u0938\u0915\u0924\u0940 \u0939\u0948\u0964",
    "quiz_data": "[{\"question\": \"\\u0932\\u094b\\u0921 \\u091f\\u0947\\u0938\\u094d\\u091f\\u093f\\u0902\\u0917 \\u092e\\u0936\\u0940\\u0928 \\u0915\\u093e \\u092e\\u0941\\u0916\\u094d\\u092f \\u0915\\u093e\\u0930\\u094d\\u092f \\u0915\\u094d\\u092f\\u093e \\u0939\\u0948?\", \"options\": [\"A) \\u0935\\u093f\\u0936\\u093f\\u0937\\u094d\\u091f \\u0932\\u0902\\u092c\\u093e\\u0908 \\u092a\\u0930 \\u092d\\u093e\\u0930 \\u0915\\u094b \\u092e\\u093e\\u092a\\u0928\\u093e\", \"B) \\u0935\\u0938\\u094d\\u0924\\u0941 \\u0915\\u0940 \\u0932\\u0902\\u092c\\u093e\\u0908 \\u0915\\u094b \\u092e\\u093e\\u092a\\u0928\\u093e\", \"C) \\u0935\\u0938\\u094d\\u0924\\u0941 \\u0915\\u0947 \\u0935\\u091c\\u0928 \\u0915\\u094b \\u092e\\u093e\\u092a\\u0928\\u093e\", \"D) \\u092e\\u0936\\u0940\\u0928 \\u0915\\u0940 \\u0917\\u0924\\u093f \\u0915\\u094b \\u092e\\u093e\\u092a\\u0928\\u093e\"], \"correct_answer\": \"A) \\u0935\\u093f\\u0936\\u093f\\u0937\\u094d\\u091f \\u0932\\u0902\\u092c\\u093e\\u0908 \\u092a\\u0930 \\u092d\\u093e\\u0930 \\u0915\\u094b \\u092e\\u093e\\u092a\\u0928\\u093e\", \"explanation\": \"\\u0932\\u094b\\u0921 \\u091f\\u0947\\u0938\\u094d\\u091f\\u093f\\u0902\\u0917 \\u092e\\u0936\\u0940\\u0928 \\u0915\\u093e \\u092e\\u0941\\u0916\\u094d\\u092f \\u0915\\u093e\\u0930\\u094d\\u092f \\u0935\\u093f\\u0936\\u093f\\u0937\\u094d\\u091f \\u0932\\u0902\\u092c\\u093e\\u0908 \\u092a\\u0930 \\u092d\\u093e\\u0930 \\u0915\\u094b \\u092e\\u093e\\u092a\\u0928\\u093e \\u0939\\u0948, \\u091c\\u0948\\u0938\\u093e \\u0915\\u093f \\u0935\\u0940\\u0921\\u093f\\u092f\\u094b \\u092e\\u0947\\u0902 \\u0926\\u093f\\u0916\\u093e\\u092f\\u093e \\u0917\\u092f\\u093e \\u0939\\u0948\\u0964\"}, {\"question\": \"\\u0932\\u094b\\u0921 \\u091f\\u0947\\u0938\\u094d\\u091f\\u093f\\u0902\\u0917 \\u092e\\u0936\\u0940\\u0928 \\u0915\\u094b \\u0915\\u0948\\u0938\\u0947 \\u0915\\u0948\\u0932\\u093f\\u092c\\u094d\\u0930\\u0947\\u091f \\u0915\\u093f\\u092f\\u093e \\u091c\\u093e\\u0924\\u093e \\u0939\\u0948?\", \"options\": [\"A) \\u0932\\u0902\\u092c\\u093e\\u0908 \\u0915\\u094b \\u0936\\u0942\\u0928\\u094d\\u092f \\u0915\\u0930\\u0928\\u0947 \\u0915\\u0947 \\u0932\\u093f\\u090f \\u092c\\u091f\\u0928 \\u0915\\u094b \\u0926\\u092c\\u093e\\u0928\\u093e\", \"B) \\u092d\\u093e\\u0930 \\u0915\\u094b \\u0936\\u0942\\u0928\\u094d\\u092f \\u0915\\u0930\\u0928\\u0947 \\u0915\\u0947 \\u0932\\u093f\\u090f \\u092c\\u091f\\u0928 \\u0915\\u094b \\u0926\\u092c\\u093e\\u0928\\u093e\", \"C) \\u0935\\u0938\\u094d\\u0924\\u0941 \\u0915\\u094b \\u092e\\u0936\\u0940\\u0928 \\u092a\\u0930 \\u0930\\u0916\\u0928\\u093e\", \"D) \\u092e\\u0936\\u0940\\u0928 \\u0915\\u094b \\u091a\\u093e\\u0932\\u0942 \\u0915\\u0930\\u0928\\u093e\"], \"correct_answer\": \"A) \\u0932\\u0902\\u092c\\u093e\\u0908 \\u0915\\u094b \\u0936\\u0942\\u0928\\u094d\\u092f \\u0915\\u0930\\u0928\\u0947 \\u0915\\u0947 \\u0932\\u093f\\u090f \\u092c\\u091f\\u0928 \\u0915\\u094b \\u0926\\u092c\\u093e\\u0928\\u093e\", \"explanation\": \"\\u0932\\u094b\\u0921 \\u091f\\u0947\\u0938\\u094d\\u091f\\u093f\\u0902\\u0917 \\u092e\\u0936\\u0940\\u0928 \\u0915\\u094b \\u0915\\u0948\\u0932\\u093f\\u092c\\u094d\\u0930\\u0947\\u091f \\u0915\\u0930\\u0928\\u0947 \\u0915\\u0947 \\u0932\\u093f\\u090f, \\u0932\\u0902\\u092c\\u093e\\u0908 \\u0915\\u094b \\u0936\\u0942\\u0928\\u094d\\u092f \\u0915\\u0930\\u0928\\u0947 \\u0915\\u0947 \\u0932\\u093f\\u090f \\u092c\\u091f\\u0928 \\u0915\\u094b \\u0926\\u092c\\u093e\\u0928\\u093e \\u0939\\u094b\\u0924\\u093e \\u0939\\u0948, \\u091c\\u0948\\u0938\\u093e \\u0915\\u093f \\u0935\\u0940\\u0921\\u093f\\u092f\\u094b \\u092e\\u0947\\u0902 \\u0926\\u093f\\u0916\\u093e\\u092f\\u093e \\u0917\\u092f\\u093e \\u0939\\u0948\\u0964\"}, {\"question\": \"\\u0932\\u094b\\u0921 \\u091f\\u0947\\u0938\\u094d\\u091f\\u093f\\u0902\\u0917 \\u092e\\u0936\\u0940\\u0928 \\u092e\\u0947\\u0902 \\u0915\\u094d\\u092f\\u093e \\u0907\\u0915\\u093e\\u0908 \\u092e\\u0947\\u0902 \\u092d\\u093e\\u0930 \\u0915\\u094b \\u092e\\u093e\\u092a\\u093e \\u091c\\u093e\\u0924\\u093e \\u0939\\u0948?\", \"options\": [\"A) \\u0917\\u094d\\u0930\\u093e\\u092e\", \"B) \\u0915\\u093f\\u0932\\u094b\\u0917\\u094d\\u0930\\u093e\\u092e\", \"C) \\u092e\\u093f\\u0932\\u0940\\u0917\\u094d\\u0930\\u093e\\u092e\", \"D) \\u091f\\u0928\"], \"correct_answer\": \"B) \\u0915\\u093f\\u0932\\u094b\\u0917\\u094d\\u0930\\u093e\\u092e\", \"explanation\": \"\\u0932\\u094b\\u0921 \\u091f\\u0947\\u0938\\u094d\\u091f\\u093f\\u0902\\u0917 \\u092e\\u0936\\u0940\\u0928 \\u092e\\u0947\\u0902 \\u092d\\u093e\\u0930 \\u0915\\u094b \\u0915\\u093f\\u0932\\u094b\\u0917\\u094d\\u0930\\u093e\\u092e \\u092e\\u0947\\u0902 \\u092e\\u093e\\u092a\\u093e \\u091c\\u093e\\u0924\\u093e \\u0939\\u0948, \\u091c\\u0948\\u0938\\u093e \\u0915\\u093f \\u0935\\u0940\\u0921\\u093f\\u092f\\u094b \\u092e\\u0947\\u0902 \\u0926\\u093f\\u0916\\u093e\\u092f\\u093e \\u0917\\u092f\\u093e \\u0939\\u0948\\u0964\"}, {\"question\": \"\\u0932\\u094b\\u0921 \\u091f\\u0947\\u0938\\u094d\\u091f\\u093f\\u0902\\u0917 \\u092e\\u0936\\u0940\\u0928 \\u0915\\u0947 \\u092a\\u0930\\u093f\\u0923\\u093e\\u092e \\u0915\\u094b \\u0915\\u0948\\u0938\\u0947 \\u0926\\u0930\\u094d\\u091c \\u0915\\u093f\\u092f\\u093e \\u091c\\u093e\\u0924\\u093e \\u0939\\u0948?\", \"options\": [\"A) \\u092e\\u0936\\u0940\\u0928 \\u092a\\u0930 \\u092a\\u094d\\u0930\\u093f\\u0902\\u091f \\u0915\\u0930\\u0928\\u093e\", \"B) \\u0915\\u093e\\u0917\\u091c \\u092a\\u0930 \\u0932\\u093f\\u0916\\u0928\\u093e\", \"C) \\u0915\\u0902\\u092a\\u094d\\u092f\\u0942\\u091f\\u0930 \\u092e\\u0947\\u0902 \\u0926\\u0930\\u094d\\u091c \\u0915\\u0930\\u0928\\u093e\", \"D) \\u092b\\u094b\\u091f\\u094b \\u0916\\u0940\\u0902\\u091a\\u0928\\u093e\"], \"correct_answer\": \"B) \\u0915\\u093e\\u0917\\u091c \\u092a\\u0930 \\u0932\\u093f\\u0916\\u0928\\u093e\", \"explanation\": \"\\u0932\\u094b\\u0921 \\u091f\\u0947\\u0938\\u094d\\u091f\\u093f\\u0902\\u0917 \\u092e\\u0936\\u0940\\u0928 \\u0915\\u0947 \\u092a\\u0930\\u093f\\u0923\\u093e\\u092e \\u0915\\u094b \\u0915\\u093e\\u0917\\u091c \\u092a\\u0930 \\u0932\\u093f\\u0916\\u0928\\u093e \\u0939\\u094b\\u0924\\u093e \\u0939\\u0948, \\u091c\\u0948\\u0938\\u093e \\u0915\\u093f \\u0935\\u0940\\u0921\\u093f\\u092f\\u094b \\u092e\\u0947\\u0902 \\u0926\\u093f\\u0916\\u093e\\u092f\\u093e \\u0917\\u092f\\u093e \\u0939\\u0948\\u0964\"}, {\"question\": \"\\u0932\\u094b\\u0921 \\u091f\\u0947\\u0938\\u094d\\u091f\\u093f\\u0902\\u0917 \\u092e\\u0936\\u0940\\u0928 \\u092e\\u0947\\u0902 \\u0915\\u094d\\u092f\\u093e \\u0918\\u091f\\u0915 \\u0939\\u094b\\u0924\\u093e \\u0939\\u0948 \\u091c\\u094b \\u092d\\u093e\\u0930 \\u0915\\u094b \\u092e\\u093e\\u092a\\u0924\\u093e \\u0939\\u0948?\", \"options\": [\"A) \\u0932\\u094b\\u0921 \\u0938\\u0947\\u0932\", \"B) \\u0938\\u094d\\u092a\\u094d\\u0930\\u093f\\u0902\\u0917\", \"C) \\u092c\\u0947\\u0938 \\u092a\\u094d\\u0932\\u0947\\u091f\", \"D) \\u092e\\u094b\\u091f\\u0930\"], \"correct_answer\": \"A) \\u0932\\u094b\\u0921 \\u0938\\u0947\\u0932\", \"explanation\": \"\\u0932\\u094b\\u0921 \\u091f\\u0947\\u0938\\u094d\\u091f\\u093f\\u0902\\u0917 \\u092e\\u0936\\u0940\\u0928 \\u092e\\u0947\\u0902 \\u0932\\u094b\\u0921 \\u0938\\u0947\\u0932 \\u0939\\u094b\\u0924\\u093e \\u0939\\u0948 \\u091c\\u094b \\u092d\\u093e\\u0930 \\u0915\\u094b \\u092e\\u093e\\u092a\\u0924\\u093e \\u0939\\u0948, \\u091c\\u0948\\u0938\\u093e \\u0915\\u093f \\u0935\\u0940\\u0921\\u093f\\u092f\\u094b \\u092e\\u0947\\u0902 \\u0926\\u093f\\u0916\\u093e\\u092f\\u093e \\u0917\\u092f\\u093e \\u0939\\u0948\\u0964\"}]",
    "is_processing": false
  },
  {
    "id": 17,
    "title": "Inprocess FPA",
    "description": "This is a module on First Part Approval: FPA",
    "video_url": "http://localhost:8000/static/videos/d83fb3bc-8454-4a5d-a090-d24a3c8ccf38.MOV",
    "created_by_id": 1,
    "objectives": "## Objectives\n- Understand the process of setting up and approving work orders, including in-process dimensions and final specifications.\n- Learn how to analyze and meet customer specifications through a First Part Approval (FPA) process or setting approval process.\n- Identify the various stages involved in the manufacturing process, including heat treatment, grinding, and washing, and how they impact the final product dimensions.\n- Develop skills in measuring and checking the final product dimensions against customer specifications using various tools such as vernier calipers and height gauges.\n- Apply knowledge of quality control processes to ensure that the final product meets the required specifications and standards.",
    "applications": "## Definitions\n- **In Process**: The stage of production where the product is being manufactured and dimensions are being checked.\n- **FPA (First Part Approval)**: A process of approving the first part of a production run to ensure it meets customer specifications.\n- **Setup Approval**: The process of approving the setup of a production line before starting production.\n- **Sampling**: The process of selecting a representative sample of products to check for quality and dimensions.\n- **Heat Treatment**: A process of treating materials with heat to alter their properties.\n- **Grinding**: A process of smoothing or polishing surfaces.\n- **Customer Specification**: The requirements and standards set by the customer for the product.\n\n## Practical Application\n- Using FPA (First Part Approval) to ensure that the product meets customer specifications before starting full production.\n- Implementing a setup approval process to ensure that the production line is set up correctly before starting production.\n- Conducting regular sampling to check the quality and dimensions of products during production.\n- Using heat treatment and grinding processes to alter the properties of materials and smooth surfaces.\n- Checking products against customer specifications using various measurement tools such as vernier calipers and height gauges.\n- Using a sampling base to fix the dimensions of products during the in-process stage.\n- Meeting customer specifications by ensuring that the final product dimensions are within the specified tolerances.\n- Using burnier and height gauge to check the length of products.\n- Applying quality control processes such as checking the spring rate, parallelism, perpendicularity, and pitch of products to ensure they meet customer specifications.",
    "quiz_data": "[{\"question\": \"What is the primary purpose of First Part Approval (FPA) in the manufacturing process?\", \"options\": [\"A) To inspect the final product\", \"B) To ensure that the in-process dimensions meet the customer's specifications\", \"C) To conduct heat treatment\", \"D) To perform grinding and washing\"], \"correct_answer\": \"B) To ensure that the in-process dimensions meet the customer's specifications\", \"explanation\": \"FPA is used to analyze the sampling and ensure that it meets the customer's specifications before proceeding with the production process.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the next step after setting up the in-process dimensions in the work order?\", \"options\": [\"A) Heat treatment\", \"B) Grinding and washing\", \"C) Setting approval process or FPA\", \"D) Final inspection\"], \"correct_answer\": \"C) Setting approval process or FPA\", \"explanation\": \"After setting up the in-process dimensions, the next step is to conduct the setting approval process or FPA to ensure that the dimensions meet the customer's specifications.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the purpose of conducting a sampling base in the in-process stage?\", \"options\": [\"A) To inspect the final product\", \"B) To analyze the dimensions and ensure they meet the customer's specifications\", \"C) To conduct heat treatment\", \"D) To perform grinding and washing\"], \"correct_answer\": \"B) To analyze the dimensions and ensure they meet the customer's specifications\", \"explanation\": \"Conducting a sampling base in the in-process stage allows for the analysis of dimensions to ensure they meet the customer's specifications.\"}, {\"question\": \"What processes are typically involved after the in-process stage?\", \"options\": [\"A) Heat treatment, grinding, and washing\", \"B) Inspection, packaging, and shipping\", \"C) Machining, assembly, and testing\", \"D) Design, prototyping, and validation\"], \"correct_answer\": \"A) Heat treatment, grinding, and washing\", \"explanation\": \"After the in-process stage, the part typically undergoes heat treatment, grinding, and washing before being inspected and shipped to the customer.\"}, {\"question\": \"How is the final dimension of the product checked against the customer's specifications?\", \"options\": [\"A) Using a vernier caliper\", \"B) Using a height gauge\", \"C) Using both vernier caliper and height gauge\", \"D) Using a micrometer\"], \"correct_answer\": \"C) Using both vernier caliper and height gauge\", \"explanation\": \"Both vernier caliper and height gauge can be used to check the final dimension of the product against the customer's specifications.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the purpose of checking the final product's dimensions against the customer's specifications?\", \"options\": [\"A) To ensure that the product meets the customer's requirements\", \"B) To identify any defects or irregularities\", \"C) To determine the product's quality\", \"D) To all of the above\"], \"correct_answer\": \"D) To all of the above\", \"explanation\": \"Checking the final product's dimensions against the customer's specifications is crucial to ensure that the product meets the customer's requirements, identify any defects or irregularities, and determine the product's quality.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the significance of the 'plus' and 'minus' values in the customer's specifications?\", \"options\": [\"A) They represent the acceptable range of dimensions\", \"B) They represent the maximum and minimum values of the dimension\", \"C) They represent the average and standard deviation of the dimension\", \"D) They are not relevant to the manufacturing process\"], \"correct_answer\": \"A) They represent the acceptable range of dimensions\", \"explanation\": \"The 'plus' and 'minus' values in the customer's specifications represent the acceptable range of dimensions, within which the product's dimensions must fall to meet the customer's requirements.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the purpose of the 'setup approval' or 'FPA' process?\", \"options\": [\"A) To inspect the final product\", \"B) To analyze the in-process dimensions and ensure they meet the customer's specifications\", \"C) To conduct heat treatment and grinding\", \"D) To perform washing and packaging\"], \"correct_answer\": \"B) To analyze the in-process dimensions and ensure they meet the customer's specifications\", \"explanation\": \"The setup approval or FPA process is used to analyze the in-process dimensions and ensure they meet the customer's specifications before proceeding with the production process.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the benefit of using a sampling base in the in-process stage?\", \"options\": [\"A) It reduces the production time\", \"B) It increases the product's quality\", \"C) It ensures that the product meets the customer's specifications\", \"D) It reduces the production cost\"], \"correct_answer\": \"C) It ensures that the product meets the customer's specifications\", \"explanation\": \"Using a sampling base in the in-process stage helps to ensure that the product meets the customer's specifications by analyzing the dimensions and making any necessary adjustments before proceeding with the production process.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the final step in the manufacturing process after the product has undergone heat treatment, grinding, and washing?\", \"options\": [\"A) Inspection and packaging\", \"B) Shipping to the customer\", \"C) Storage and inventory management\", \"D) Quality control and assurance\"], \"correct_answer\": \"A) Inspection and packaging\", \"explanation\": \"After the product has undergone heat treatment, grinding, and washing, the final step is to inspect the product to ensure it meets the customer's specifications and package it for shipping.\"}]",
    "is_processing": false
  },
  {
    "id": 18,
    "title": "In process FPA",
    "description": "This is a module on Inprocess FPA",
    "video_url": "http://localhost:8000/static/videos/83074cfe-a890-4dee-bf12-9de828dada45.MOV",
    "created_by_id": 1,
    "objectives": "## Objectives\n- Understand the process of setting up and approving work orders, including the use of sampling and First Part Approval (FPA) to ensure compliance with customer specifications.\n- Learn how to analyze and verify the dimensions of parts during the production process, including the use of various measurement tools such as vernier calipers and height gauges.\n- Identify the key steps involved in the production process, including heat treatment, grinding, and washing, and how these steps affect the final dimensions of the parts.\n- Understand how to compare the final dimensions of parts with customer specifications and verify that they meet the required tolerances.\n- Develop skills in using measurement tools and techniques to check the dimensions of parts and ensure that they meet customer requirements.",
    "applications": "## Definitions\n- **In Process**: The stage of production where the product is being manufactured and its dimensions are being checked and adjusted.\n- **FPA (First Part Approval)**: A process of approving the first part of a production run to ensure it meets the customer's specifications.\n- **Sampling**: The process of selecting a representative sample of products to check for quality and dimensions.\n- **Heat Treatment**: A process of treating materials with heat to alter their properties.\n- **Grinding**: A process of smoothing or polishing the surface of a material.\n- **Customer Specification**: The requirements and standards set by the customer for the product.\n\n## Practical Application\n- Real-world usage examples of in-process dimension checking, such as using vernier calipers to measure the diameter and length of a product.\n- Application of FPA process to ensure the first part of a production run meets the customer's specifications.\n- Use of sampling to check the quality and dimensions of products during the manufacturing process.\n- Implementation of heat treatment and grinding processes to alter the properties and smooth the surface of materials.\n- Checking of final products against customer specifications to ensure they meet the required standards.\n- Use of measuring instruments such as vernier calipers, height gauges, and burnier to check the dimensions of products.\n- Example of a production process involving multiple stages, including heat treatment, grinding, washing, and final inspection.",
    "quiz_data": "[{\"question\": \"What is the primary purpose of the FPA (First Part Approval) process in the context of in-process dimension control?\", \"options\": [\"A) To inspect the final product\", \"B) To analyze and approve the sampling process\", \"C) To conduct heat treatment\", \"D) To perform grinding and washing\"], \"correct_answer\": \"B) To analyze and approve the sampling process\", \"explanation\": \"The FPA process is used to analyze and approve the sampling process to ensure that it meets the customer's specifications.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the purpose of setting up a 'setup approval' or 'FPA' before manufacturing a part?\", \"options\": [\"A) To inspect the final product\", \"B) To analyze and approve the sampling process\", \"C) To ensure that the part meets the customer's specifications\", \"D) To conduct heat treatment and grinding\"], \"correct_answer\": \"C) To ensure that the part meets the customer's specifications\", \"explanation\": \"The setup approval or FPA is used to ensure that the part meets the customer's specifications before manufacturing begins.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the next step after the sampling process in the in-process dimension control?\", \"options\": [\"A) Heat treatment\", \"B) Grinding and washing\", \"C) Final inspection\", \"D) Packaging and shipping\"], \"correct_answer\": \"A) Heat treatment\", \"explanation\": \"After the sampling process, the next step is heat treatment, followed by grinding, washing, and other processes.\"}, {\"question\": \"How is the final dimension of the product checked to ensure it meets the customer's specifications?\", \"options\": [\"A) Using a vernier caliper\", \"B) Using a height gauge\", \"C) Using both vernier caliper and height gauge\", \"D) Using only visual inspection\"], \"correct_answer\": \"C) Using both vernier caliper and height gauge\", \"explanation\": \"Both vernier caliper and height gauge can be used to check the final dimension of the product to ensure it meets the customer's specifications.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the purpose of checking the length of the product using a height gauge or vernier caliper?\", \"options\": [\"A) To ensure it meets the customer's specifications\", \"B) To conduct heat treatment\", \"C) To perform grinding and washing\", \"D) To inspect the final product\"], \"correct_answer\": \"A) To ensure it meets the customer's specifications\", \"explanation\": \"The purpose of checking the length of the product using a height gauge or vernier caliper is to ensure that it meets the customer's specifications.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the tolerance for the ID (Inner Diameter) of the product according to the customer's specifications?\", \"options\": [\"A) 12 +/- 0.15\", \"B) 12 +/- 0.12\", \"C) 12 +/- 0.10\", \"D) 12 +/- 0.05\"], \"correct_answer\": \"A) 12 +/- 0.15\", \"explanation\": \"The customer's specification for the ID is 12 +/- 0.15.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the result of the final dimension check of the product's ID?\", \"options\": [\"A) 11.98, which is out of tolerance\", \"B) 12.02, which is within tolerance\", \"C) 12.05, which is out of tolerance\", \"D) 11.95, which is out of tolerance\"], \"correct_answer\": \"B) 12.02, which is within tolerance\", \"explanation\": \"The final dimension check of the product's ID shows a result of 12.02, which is within the tolerance of 12 +/- 0.15.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the purpose of the 'in-process' dimension control?\", \"options\": [\"A) To inspect the final product\", \"B) To analyze and approve the sampling process\", \"C) To ensure that the product meets the customer's specifications during manufacturing\", \"D) To conduct heat treatment and grinding\"], \"correct_answer\": \"C) To ensure that the product meets the customer's specifications during manufacturing\", \"explanation\": \"The purpose of the 'in-process' dimension control is to ensure that the product meets the customer's specifications during manufacturing.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the sequence of processes after the sampling process in the in-process dimension control?\", \"options\": [\"A) Heat treatment, grinding, washing, and final inspection\", \"B) Grinding, washing, heat treatment, and final inspection\", \"C) Washing, heat treatment, grinding, and final inspection\", \"D) Final inspection, heat treatment, grinding, and washing\"], \"correct_answer\": \"A) Heat treatment, grinding, washing, and final inspection\", \"explanation\": \"The sequence of processes after the sampling process is heat treatment, followed by grinding, washing, and final inspection.\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the result of comparing the final dimension of the product with the customer's specifications?\", \"options\": [\"A) The final dimension is out of tolerance\", \"B) The final dimension is within tolerance\", \"C) The final dimension is not checked\", \"D) The customer's specifications are not available\"], \"correct_answer\": \"B) The final dimension is within tolerance\", \"explanation\": \"The final dimension of the product is compared with the customer's specifications, and the result shows that it is within tolerance.\"}]",
    "is_processing": false
  },
  {
    "id": 23,
    "title": "Work order, QA document and Rejection Reporting 6",
    "description": "Work order, QA document and Rejection Reporting",
    "video_url": "http://localhost:8000/static/videos/50722f96-ca18-438d-a63a-56281989866b.mp4",
    "created_by_id": 1,
    "objectives": "## Objectives\n- Understand the process of creating a work order based on customer drawings and specifications\n- Learn how to identify and document key parameters such as metal type, wire dye, ID, number of turns, and length in a work order\n- Familiarize with the in-process inspection procedure, including verifying part dimensions and specifications at regular intervals\n- Understand the process of addressing out-of-spec parts, including rework, segregation, and scrap tagging\n- Learn how to complete a scrap tag with relevant information, including item number, work order number, customer, reason for scrap, and other details",
    "applications": "## Definitions\n- **Work Order**: A document that outlines the specifications and requirements for a particular job or project, based on the customer's drawing and specifications.\n- **Customer Specification**: The requirements and parameters specified by the customer for a particular product or job, including dimensions, materials, and other relevant details.\n- **In-Process Inspection**: The process of inspecting and verifying the product or job at various stages of production to ensure that it meets the required specifications and standards.\n- **Quality Inspector**: A person responsible for inspecting and verifying the product or job to ensure that it meets the required specifications and standards.\n- **Red Tag**: A tag or label used to identify and segregate defective or non-conforming products or materials.\n- **Reworkable**: Products or materials that can be reworked or repaired to meet the required specifications and standards.\n- **Scrap**: Products or materials that are defective or non-conforming and cannot be reworked or repaired, and are therefore discarded.\n\n## Practical Application\n- Creating a work order based on the customer's drawing and specifications to ensure that the product or job meets the required requirements.\n- Conducting in-process inspections at regular intervals (e.g. every 2 hours) to verify that the product or job meets the required specifications and standards.\n- Using a red tag system to identify and segregate defective or non-conforming products or materials.\n- Maintaining a record of defective or non-conforming products or materials, including the reason for rejection and the quantity rejected.\n- Implementing a rework process for products or materials that can be reworked or repaired to meet the required specifications and standards.\n- Discarding scrap products or materials that are defective or non-conforming and cannot be reworked or repaired.\n- Using a quality control process to ensure that products or jobs meet the required specifications and standards, and to identify and correct any defects or non-conformities.",
    "quiz_data": "[{\"question\":\"What is the primary basis for preparing a work order?\",\"type\":\"mcq\",\"options\":[\"A) Customer specification\",\"B) Operator preference\",\"C) Machine capability\",\"D) Material availability\"],\"correct_answer\":\"A) Customer specification\",\"explanation\":\"The work order is prepared based on the customer's drawing and specifications.\",\"module_index\":0},{\"question\":\"What information is typically included in a work order?\",\"type\":\"mcq\",\"options\":[\"A) Only customer name and number\",\"B) Machine setup and operator details\",\"C) Customer specifications, such as metal use, wire dye, and number of turns\",\"D) Production schedule and deadline\"],\"correct_answer\":\"C) Customer specifications, such as metal use, wire dye, and number of turns\",\"explanation\":\"The work order includes all the parameters mentioned in the customer's drawing, such as metal use, wire dye, ID, number of turns, and length.\",\"module_index\":0},{\"question\":\"What is the purpose of releasing the work order to production?\",\"type\":\"mcq\",\"options\":[\"A) To confirm the customer's order\",\"B) To prepare the machine setup and operator details\",\"C) To ensure that the operator meets the customer's specifications\",\"D) To finalize the production schedule\"],\"correct_answer\":\"C) To ensure that the operator meets the customer's specifications\",\"explanation\":\"The work order is released to production so that the operator can set up the machine and ensure that the final product meets the customer's specifications.\",\"module_index\":0},{\"question\":\"What is the final step after the work order is prepared and released to production?\",\"type\":\"mcq\",\"options\":[\"A) Machine setup and operation\",\"B) Quality control and inspection\",\"C) Customer feedback and review\",\"D) Validation of the final product against the customer's specifications\"],\"correct_answer\":\"D) Validation of the final product against the customer's specifications\",\"explanation\":\"The final step is to validate the final product against the customer's specifications to ensure that it meets all the required parameters.\",\"module_index\":0},{\"question\":\"What is the primary purpose of in-process inspection?\",\"type\":\"mcq\",\"options\":[\"A) To validate the final product\",\"B) To monitor and control the production process\",\"C) To inspect the raw materials\",\"D) To package the final product\"],\"correct_answer\":\"B) To monitor and control the production process\",\"explanation\":\"In-process inspection is used to monitor and control the production process to ensure that the product meets the required specifications.\",\"module_index\":1},{\"question\":\"What dimensions are typically checked during in-process inspection?\",\"type\":\"mcq\",\"options\":[\"A) Only outer diameter\",\"B) Only inner diameter\",\"C) Outer diameter, inner diameter, free length, number of turns, and direction\",\"D) None of the above\"],\"correct_answer\":\"C) Outer diameter, inner diameter, free length, number of turns, and direction\",\"explanation\":\"During in-process inspection, various dimensions such as outer diameter, inner diameter, free length, number of turns, and direction are typically checked.\",\"module_index\":1},{\"question\":\"How often does the quality inspector verify the part during production?\",\"type\":\"mcq\",\"options\":[\"A) Every hour\",\"B) Every 2 hours\",\"C) Every 4 hours\",\"D) Only at the end of production\"],\"correct_answer\":\"B) Every 2 hours\",\"explanation\":\"The quality inspector verifies the part every 2 hours during production to ensure that it meets the required specifications.\",\"module_index\":1},{\"question\":\"What information is typically included in the in-process inspection specification?\",\"type\":\"mcq\",\"options\":[\"A) Only the product description\",\"B) Only the production schedule\",\"C) Machine number, work order number, item description, quantity, size, and specification\",\"D) None of the above\"],\"correct_answer\":\"C) Machine number, work order number, item description, quantity, size, and specification\",\"explanation\":\"The in-process inspection specification typically includes detailed information such as machine number, work order number, item description, quantity, size, and specification.\",\"module_index\":1},{\"question\":\"What is the purpose of rejection reporting in scrap management?\",\"type\":\"mcq\",\"options\":[\"A) To track customer complaints\",\"B) To identify and document defective products\",\"C) To monitor production schedules\",\"D) To manage inventory levels\"],\"correct_answer\":\"B) To identify and document defective products\",\"explanation\":\"Rejection reporting is a critical step in scrap management, as it helps to identify and document defective products, allowing for prompt action to be taken to prevent further defects.\",\"module_index\":2},{\"question\":\"What information is typically included in a rejection report?\",\"type\":\"mcq\",\"options\":[\"A) Customer name, work order number, and date\",\"B) Product description, quantity, and defect type\",\"C) All of the above\",\"D) None of the above\"],\"correct_answer\":\"C) All of the above\",\"explanation\":\"A rejection report typically includes information such as customer name, work order number, date, product description, quantity, and defect type, in order to provide a comprehensive record of the defective product.\",\"module_index\":2},{\"question\":\"What is the purpose of a red tag in scrap management?\",\"type\":\"mcq\",\"options\":[\"A) To indicate a product that is ready for shipment\",\"B) To identify a product that is defective and cannot be reworked\",\"C) To track inventory levels\",\"D) To monitor production schedules\"],\"correct_answer\":\"B) To identify a product that is defective and cannot be reworked\",\"explanation\":\"A red tag is used to indicate a product that is defective and cannot be reworked, allowing for clear identification and segregation of defective products.\",\"module_index\":2},{\"question\":\"What happens to a product that is identified as out of spec during the inspection process?\",\"type\":\"mcq\",\"options\":[\"A) It is shipped to the customer\",\"B) It is reworked to meet specifications\",\"C) It is scrapped and a rejection report is generated\",\"D) It is placed on hold for further evaluation\"],\"correct_answer\":\"C) It is scrapped and a rejection report is generated\",\"explanation\":\"If a product is identified as out of spec during the inspection process, it is typically scrapped and a rejection report is generated to document the defect and prevent further defects.\",\"module_index\":2},{\"question\":\"what is the ID of sample A?\",\"type\":\"numerical\",\"options\":[],\"correct_answer\":\"5.33\",\"explanation\":\"Explanation here\",\"tolerance\":0.03}]",
    "is_processing": false
  },
  {
    "id": 25,
    "title": "Plug Gauge",
    "description": "Plug Gauge",
    "video_url": "http://localhost:8000/static/videos/94699267-91d3-42cc-a906-75a30c353589.mp4",
    "created_by_id": 1,
    "objectives": "## Objectives\n- Understand the role and purpose of a plug gage in measuring ID (Inner Diameter) in a production process\n- Learn how to interpret and apply customer specifications and in-process specifications for ID measurement\n- Understand the concept of \"go\" and \"no-go\" gauging in quality control, including how to use plug gages to determine whether a product meets specifications\n- Apply the knowledge of plug gage usage in mass production to train operators and quality inspectors\n- Familiarize with the process of using plug gages for quality control in manufacturing, including the importance of accurate measurement and inspection",
    "applications": "## Definitions\n- **\u092a\u094d\u0932\u0917 \u0917\u0947\u091c (Plug Gage)**: \u090f\u0915 \u0909\u092a\u0915\u0930\u0923 \u091c\u093f\u0938\u0915\u093e \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u0906\u0908\u0921\u0940 (\u0906\u0902\u0924\u0930\u093f\u0915 \u0935\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938) \u0915\u094b \u092e\u093e\u092a\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0947 \u0932\u093f\u090f \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948\u0964\n- **\u0917\u094b \u0928\u0949\u091f \u0917\u094b (Go Not Go)**: \u090f\u0915 \u092e\u093e\u092a\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0940 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0923\u093e\u0932\u0940 \u091c\u093f\u0938\u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0926\u094b \u0938\u0940\u092e\u093e\u090f\u0902 \u0939\u094b\u0924\u0940 \u0939\u0948\u0902, \u090f\u0915 \u091c\u094b \u092e\u093e\u0928\u0915 \u0915\u0947 \u0905\u0928\u0941\u0938\u093e\u0930 \u0939\u094b\u0928\u0940 \u091a\u093e\u0939\u093f\u090f (\u0917\u094b) \u0914\u0930 \u090f\u0915 \u091c\u094b \u092e\u093e\u0928\u0915 \u0915\u0947 \u0905\u0928\u0941\u0938\u093e\u0930 \u0928\u0939\u0940\u0902 \u0939\u094b\u0928\u0940 \u091a\u093e\u0939\u093f\u090f (\u0928\u0949\u091f \u0917\u094b)\u0964\n- **\u0907\u0928 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u094b\u0938\u0947\u0938**: \u0909\u0924\u094d\u092a\u093e\u0926\u0928 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0915\u094d\u0930\u093f\u092f\u093e \u0915\u0947 \u0926\u094c\u0930\u093e\u0928 \u0917\u0941\u0923\u0935\u0924\u094d\u0924\u093e \u0928\u093f\u092f\u0902\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0923 \u0915\u0940 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0915\u094d\u0930\u093f\u092f\u093e\u0964\n- **\u092b\u093e\u0907\u0928\u0932**: \u0909\u0924\u094d\u092a\u093e\u0926\u0928 \u0915\u0947 \u0905\u0902\u0924\u093f\u092e \u091a\u0930\u0923 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0917\u0941\u0923\u0935\u0924\u094d\u0924\u093e \u0928\u093f\u092f\u0902\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0923 \u0915\u0940 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0915\u094d\u0930\u093f\u092f\u093e\u0964\n\n## Practical Application\n- \u092a\u094d\u0932\u0917 \u0917\u0947\u091c \u0915\u093e \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u0909\u0924\u094d\u092a\u093e\u0926\u0928 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0915\u094d\u0930\u093f\u092f\u093e \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0906\u0908\u0921\u0940 \u0915\u094b \u092e\u093e\u092a\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0947 \u0932\u093f\u090f \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948\u0964\n- \u0917\u094b \u0928\u0949\u091f \u0917\u094b \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0923\u093e\u0932\u0940 \u0915\u093e \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u0909\u0924\u094d\u092a\u093e\u0926\u0928 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0915\u094d\u0930\u093f\u092f\u093e \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0917\u0941\u0923\u0935\u0924\u094d\u0924\u093e \u0928\u093f\u092f\u0902\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0923 \u0915\u0947 \u0932\u093f\u090f \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948, \u091c\u093f\u0938\u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0926\u094b \u0938\u0940\u092e\u093e\u090f\u0902 \u0939\u094b\u0924\u0940 \u0939\u0948\u0902 \u091c\u094b \u092e\u093e\u0928\u0915 \u0915\u0947 \u0905\u0928\u0941\u0938\u093e\u0930 \u0939\u094b\u0928\u0940 \u091a\u093e\u0939\u093f\u090f \u0914\u0930 \u0928\u0939\u0940\u0902 \u0939\u094b\u0928\u0940 \u091a\u093e\u0939\u093f\u090f\u0964\n- \u0907\u0928 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u094b\u0938\u0947\u0938 \u0917\u0941\u0923\u0935\u0924\u094d\u0924\u093e \u0928\u093f\u092f\u0902\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0923 \u0915\u093e \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u0909\u0924\u094d\u092a\u093e\u0926\u0928 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0915\u094d\u0930\u093f\u092f\u093e \u0915\u0947 \u0926\u094c\u0930\u093e\u0928 \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948 \u0924\u093e\u0915\u093f \u092f\u0939 \u0938\u0941\u0928\u093f\u0936\u094d\u091a\u093f\u0924 \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e \u0938\u0915\u0947 \u0915\u093f \u0909\u0924\u094d\u092a\u093e\u0926 \u092e\u093e\u0928\u0915 \u0915\u0947 \u0905\u0928\u0941\u0938\u093e\u0930 \u0939\u0948\u0964\n- \u092b\u093e\u0907\u0928\u0932 \u0917\u0941\u0923\u0935\u0924\u094d\u0924\u093e \u0928\u093f\u092f\u0902\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0923 \u0915\u093e \u0909\u092a\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u0909\u0924\u094d\u092a\u093e\u0926\u0928 \u0915\u0947 \u0905\u0902\u0924\u093f\u092e \u091a\u0930\u0923 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948 \u0924\u093e\u0915\u093f \u092f\u0939 \u0938\u0941\u0928\u093f\u0936\u094d\u091a\u093f\u0924 \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e \u0938\u0915\u0947 \u0915\u093f \u0909\u0924\u094d\u092a\u093e\u0926 \u0917\u094d\u0930\u093e\u0939\u0915 \u0915\u0940 \u0906\u0935\u0936\u094d\u092f\u0915\u0924\u093e\u0913\u0902 \u0915\u094b \u092a\u0942\u0930\u093e \u0915\u0930\u0924\u093e \u0939\u0948\u0964",
    "quiz_data": "[{\"question\": \"In mass production, what is the primary purpose of using a plug gauge with 'go' and 'no-go' specifications?\", \"type\": \"mcq\", \"options\": [\"A) To measure the outer diameter of a component\", \"B) To inspect the surface finish of a part\", \"C) To control the inner diameter of a component within specified tolerances\", \"D) To determine the weight of a finished product\"], \"correct_answer\": \"C) To control the inner diameter of a component within specified tolerances\", \"explanation\": \"The plug gauge is used to ensure that the inner diameter of a component falls within the specified tolerances, which is critical for maintaining quality and consistency in mass production.\", \"module_index\": 0}, {\"question\": \"What is the significance of the 'go' and 'no-go' limits in a plug gauge, such as 12.2 and 12.4, in the context of mass production?\", \"type\": \"mcq\", \"options\": [\"A) They represent the maximum and minimum allowable dimensions for a component\", \"B) They define the tolerance range for a specific feature\", \"C) They determine the sampling size for quality control inspections\", \"D) They specify the burn-in time for a component\"], \"correct_answer\": \"B) They define the tolerance range for a specific feature\", \"explanation\": \"The 'go' and 'no-go' limits define the acceptable range of dimensions for a specific feature, ensuring that the component meets the required specifications and functions as intended.\", \"module_index\": 0}, {\"question\": \"How do the 'go' and 'no-go' limits for in-process control, such as 12.2-12.4, relate to the final customer specifications, such as 12 +/- 0.15 and +/- 0.7?\", \"type\": \"mcq\", \"options\": [\"A) The in-process limits are always tighter than the final specifications\", \"B) The in-process limits are always looser than the final specifications\", \"C) The in-process limits are a subset of the final specifications, ensuring that parts meeting the in-process limits will also meet the final specifications\", \"D) The in-process limits are unrelated to the final specifications\"], \"correct_answer\": \"C) The in-process limits are a subset of the final specifications, ensuring that parts meeting the in-process limits will also meet the final specifications\", \"explanation\": \"The in-process limits are designed to be a subset of the final specifications, ensuring that parts that meet the in-process limits will also meet the final specifications, thereby reducing the risk of non-conforming parts reaching the customer.\", \"module_index\": 0}, {\"question\": \"What is the primary benefit of using a plug gauge with 'go' and 'no-go' specifications in mass production, as opposed to relying solely on variable gauging methods?\", \"type\": \"mcq\", \"options\": [\"A) Reduced inspection time and increased throughput\", \"B) Improved accuracy and reduced variability in measurements\", \"C) Enhanced operator safety and reduced risk of injury\", \"D) Simplified calibration and maintenance procedures\"], \"correct_answer\": \"B) Improved accuracy and reduced variability in measurements\", \"explanation\": \"The use of a plug gauge with 'go' and 'no-go' specifications provides a clear pass/fail criterion, reducing the variability in measurements and improving the overall accuracy of the inspection process.\", \"module_index\": 0}]",
    "is_processing": false
