    "title": "Introduction to Work Order and Customer Specifications",
    "content": "## Introduction to Work Order and Customer Specifications\n### Overview\nA work order is a document that outlines the specifications and requirements for a particular job or task. It serves as a communication tool between the customer and the production team, ensuring that the final product meets the customer's needs.\n\n### Key Components of a Work Order\n* **Customer Drawing**: The basis for creating a work order, providing detailed specifications and requirements.\n* **Customer Specifications**: Parameters mentioned in the work order, including:\n\t+ Material to be used\n\t+ Wire diameter\n\t+ Inner diameter (ID)\n\t+ Number of turns\n\t+ Length\n\t+ Other relevant details\n\n### Purpose of a Work Order\n* To provide clear instructions to the production team\n* To ensure that the final product meets customer requirements\n* To facilitate the production process by outlining the necessary specifications and parameters\n\n### Work Order Process\n1. Creation of the work order based on customer drawing and specifications\n2. Release of the work order to the production team\n3. Operator sets up the machine according to the work order specifications\n4. Production team works on the task, ensuring that the final product meets the required specifications\n\n### Importance of Accurate Work Orders\n* Ensures that the final product meets customer requirements\n* Reduces errors and rework\n* Improves communication between the customer and production team",
    "media_url": "http://localhost:8000/static/courses/10/1_Introduction_to_Work_Order_and_Customer_Specifications.mp4",
    "step_type": "instruction"
