    "title": "Introduction to Measuring Instruments and Height Gauge",
    "content": "## Introduction to Measuring Instruments and Height Gauge\n### Overview\n\nThe module covers the basics of measuring instruments, focusing on Vernier calipers and height gauges.\n\n### Key Concepts\n* **Vernier Caliper**:\n  * Used for measuring length and internal diameter (ID)\n  * Left-hand side used for length measurement\n  * Right-hand side used for ID measurement\n* **Height Gauge**:\n  * Measures height up to 300mm\n  * Procedure:\n    1. Zero the gauge by touching the base\n    2. Lift the gauge to measure the height\n    3. Take the reading\n\n### Using a Height Gauge\n1. Place the object on the surface plate\n2. Zero the height gauge on the surface plate\n3. Move the gauge up to touch the object\n4. Take the reading on the display\n\n### Key Takeaways\n* Vernier calipers and height gauges are used for precise measurements\n* Understanding the correct usage and procedure is crucial for accurate results\n* Height gauges are used for measuring heights up to 300mm\n\n### Visual Aids\nThe images demonstrate the usage of Vernier calipers and height gauges, showing the hands-on measurement process.",
    "media_url": "http://localhost:8000/static/courses/12/1_Introduction_to_Measuring_Instruments_and_Height_Gauge.mp4",
