    "title": "Introduction to Plug Gauge and its Role in Mass Production",
    "content": "## Introduction to Plug Gauge and its Role in Mass Production\n### Overview\nThe plug gauge is a precision measuring instrument used to inspect the internal diameter of cylindrical parts.\n\n### Key Concepts\n* **Purpose**: To measure the internal diameter of a part to ensure it meets specifications.\n* **Types**:\n  + Go gauge: checks if the diameter is within the lower limit.\n  + Not-go gauge: checks if the diameter is within the upper limit.\n* **Role in Mass Production**:\n  + Ensures parts are manufactured within specified tolerances.\n  + Facilitates quick inspection, reducing production time.\n  + Provides a simple, reliable method for quality control.\n\n### How it Works\n1. The plug gauge has two ends: Go and Not-go.\n2. The Go end should fit into the part, while the Not-go end should not.\n3. This ensures the internal diameter is within the acceptable range.\n\n### Specifications\n* The transcript mentions specific dimensions: 12.2 and 12.4 for in-process inspection, and 11.93 and 12.15 for final inspection.\n\n### Importance\n* Plug gauges are essential in mass production for maintaining quality and consistency.\n* They are used by both operators and quality inspectors to verify parts.\n\n### Best Practices\n* Regular calibration of plug gauges is necessary to ensure accuracy.\n* Proper handling and storage are crucial to maintain the gauge's precision.",
    "media_url": "http://localhost:8000/static/courses/15/1_Introduction_to_Plug_Gauge_and_its_Role_in_Mass_Production.mp4",
    "step_type": "instruction"
  },
