    "id": 19,
    "module_id": 16,
    "order_index": 1,
    "title": "Introduction to Load Testing Machine and Its Operating Procedure",
    "content": "## Introduction to Load Testing Machine\n### Overview\nThe Load Testing Machine is used to measure the load on a spring at a specific compression length.\n\n### Key Components\n* Load cell\n* Digital display for length and load measurement\n\n### Operating Procedure\n1. **Initial Setup**\n\t* Combine the two bases of the machine.\n\t* Zero the length measurement.\n2. **Measuring Load**\n\t* Place the spring on the load cell's base plate.\n\t* Zero the weight of the spring.\n\t* Compress the spring to the specified length.\n\t* Record the load measurement.\n3. **Example Measurement**\n\t* Specified length: 28 mm\n\t* Measured load: 1.017 kg at 28.44 mm\n\t* Measured load: 2.46 kg at 22.82 mm\n\n### Key Concepts\n* The machine measures load at a specific compression length.\n* The digital display shows both length and load measurements.\n* The operating procedure involves zeroing the length and weight measurements before taking readings.\n\n### Important Takeaways\n* The Load Testing Machine is used to verify if the load on a spring meets the specified requirements at a particular compression length.\n* The machine provides accurate digital measurements for length and load.",
    "media_url": "http://localhost:8000/static/courses/16/1_Introduction_to_Load_Testing_Machine_and_Its_Operating_Procedure.mp4",
