e dye, ID, number of turns, and length.\"},{\"question_text\":\"What is the purpose of rejection reporting in scrap management?\",\"user_answer\":\"\",\"correct_answer\":\"B) To identify and document defective products\",\"is_correct\":false,\"module_link\":\"/modules/23?step=2\",\"explanation\":\"Rejection reporting is a critical step in scrap management, as it helps to identify and document defective products, allowing for prompt action to be taken to prevent further defects.\"},{\"question_text\":\"How often does the quality inspector verify the part during production?\",\"user_answer\":\"\",\"correct_answer\":\"B) Every 2 hours\",\"is_correct\":false,\"module_link\":\"/modules/23?step=1\",\"explanation\":\"The quality inspector verifies the part every 2 hours during production to ensure that it meets the required specifications.\"},{\"question_text\":\"What dimensions are typically checked during in-process inspection?\",\"user_answer\":\"\",\"correct_answer\":\"C) Outer diameter, inner diameter, free length, number of turns, and direction\",\"is_correct\":false,\"module_link\":\"/modules/23?step=1\",\"explanation\":\"During in-process inspection, various dimensions such as outer diameter, inner diameter, free length, number of turns, and direction are typically checked.\"}]",
