sed to label products that are rejected and cannot be reworked, providing a clear indication that the product is defective and cannot be used or sold.\"},{\"question_text\":\"What information is typically included in a rejection report?\",\"user_answer\":\"C) The production schedule and employee assignments\",\"correct_answer\":\"B) The product description, quantity, reason for rejection, and customer information\",\"is_correct\":false,\"module_link\":null,\"explanation\":\"A rejection report typically includes the product description, quantity, reason for rejection, and customer information, providing a detailed record of the rejected product and the actions taken.\"},{\"question_text\":\"What is the purpose of in-process inspection?\",\"user_answer\":\"B) To monitor the production process and ensure that it meets customer specifications\",\"correct_answer\":\"B) To monitor the production process and ensure that it meets customer specifications\",\"is_correct\":true,\"module_link\":null,\"explanation\":\"In-process inspection is used to monitor the production process and ensure that it meets customer specifications, allowing for prompt identification and correction of any deviations.\"},{\"question_text\":\"What is the purpose of a rejection report?\",\"user_answer\":\"C) To record and report on products that do not meet customer specifications\",\"correct_answer\":\"C) To record and report on products that do not meet customer specifications\",\"is_correct\":true,\"module_link\":null,\"explanation\":\"A rejection report is used to record and report on products that do not meet customer specifications, providing a formal documentation of the defect and the actions taken to address it.\"},{\"question_text\":\"What is the purpose of a scrap note in the context of rejection reporting?\",\"user_answer\":\"B) To track customer complaints and feedback\",\"correct_answer\":\"C) To record and report on products that are scrapped and disposed of\",\"is_correct\":false,\"mod